### Description

There was a new feature introduced in Angular 15 about keyframes.

I observed that keyframes inside a SCSS mixin will not get the elements scope as a prefix and thus never run.
This only happens if the styling is delivered from a library. 

Example code:
```
div {
  height:100px;
  width: 200px;
  background: red;

  @include motion {
    animation: change-color 4s .2s cubic-bezier(0.075, 0.82, 0.165, 1) forwards;
  }
}

@keyframes change-color {
  from {
    background-color: blue;
  }

  to {
    background-color: green;
  }
}


```
The motion mixin in this example will add a `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) { ... }` .

I added an link to a minimal project to reproduce to bug. You need to run `npm run build lib` and afterwards `npm run start`.
The application relies on the dist folder of the library. 


